      "Flavor": "ful tea Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2026 Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? ) This Chinese black tea is looseleaf and really is best steeped in a pot to get the full flavor. Each bag makes one pot so it's quite expensive for 12 pots of tea. The flavor is very nice and it has a wonderful aroma. Individually packaged looseleaf for freshness is a quality idea. Helpful Report  Doug K 5.0 out of 5 stars  Excellent tea with balanced taste and aroma Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2026 Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? ) This black tea is said to be handpicked from old naturally grown trees in the Yunnan Province, the southern part of China. I am no expert in tea (I have a few tea experts in my family, though), but I do know what I like in tea when it’s balanced, aromatic (not perfumy or medicine), and certain pleasurable notes on the palate. I usually brew my tea with hot water, never in cold water even during the hot weather. The smell of unbrewed tea upon opening this tea bag was mild and pleasurable (not pungent) with a bit of floral aroma. For my first cup of this Liuxia tea, I brewed a whole pot of tea with one whole bag. When brewed, the color is medium-shade (became darker in the pot as it kept steeping) gold and tastes smooth and well-balanced with a hint of floral but no sweet notes, honestly a hint of wood and bitterness (but nothing to dislike about). This tea presented mild and pleasant (I can’t exactly describe what) aroma — a soft floral fragrance, maybe. Next day, I was going to brew more with the previous brew. The color of tea actually became like coffee. I took out the steeper from the teapot, then added more water and boiled, then put the steeper back in. The second pot of tea tasted almost the same, same aroma. This tells me that I don’t need to use a whole bag for the pot, maybe a 1/3 or ½. I will experiment more. For a single cup of tea, I would recommend a pinch (not a whole bag) of tea (depending upon desired strength or taste) in the cup, add 8oz of boiling water, then steep for 3-4 minutes and drink. It says the tea flavor will stay up to 5 brews; therefore, each bag will produce 5 8oz tea or make a pot of tea for several people. This tea tastes good and there’s nothing I didn’t like in the taste and aroma. It comes in a presentable red gift box with 12 packs of 3.4oz bags. It will be a good gift for tea lovers and occasional tea drinkers. Yeah, I would drink this tea every day and recommend strongly. Read more 5 people found this helpful Helpful Report  Christopher H. 5.0 out of 5 stars  Good quality black tea that you can taste Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2026 Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? ) This is probably one of the more impressively packaged and presented Chinese black tea that I've seen. Opening it up you get a pamphlet that discusses about the process and the selection of tea leaves which gives you an appreciation for what you're about to drink. On the reverse side of that is a set of certifications about the testing of these products for quality which is great as I never see this for tea leaves typically, but it shows they want to show you this is something you can trust to ingest. You get 12 individual bags of loose leave tea. When I opened the bag, I realized this is probably the amount of loose-leaf tea that you'd want to steep in a pot. I only can steep tea individually as I don't have a pot, so I only took about 1/2-2/3rds of the tea leaves and used that to steep the tea. The product says it's resistant to oversteeping so let it sit for 10 minutes rather than the 5 minutes I typically do. I'm not a tea connoisseur but I've grown up drinking a lot of black/oolong tea having at Chinese restaurants, and when I drank this tea, I'd say this is up there w/ some of the better ones I've had. It was the right amount of potency, and the flavor was just right, and it didn't taste bitter to me. I tried to reuse the tea to steep a second round, but I could tell it wasn't near as potent or as flavorful as the first steep. I'll likely have to use the remaining tea leaves within the next day to make sure I'm using it as fresh as possible. I think this makes a nice gift set for those who can appreciate tea and have the tools to steep loose leaf tea. It tastes good and it's individually packaged for maximum freshness. Read more One person found this helpful Helpful Report See more reviews Back to top Get to Know Us Careers Amazon Newsletter About Amazon Accessibility Sustainability Press Center Investor Relations Amazon Devices Amazon Science   Make Money with Us Sell on Amazon Sell apps on Amazon Supply to Amazon Protect & Build Your Brand Become an Affiliate Become a Delivery Driver Start a Package Delivery Business Advertise Your Products Self-Publish with Us Become an Amazon Hub Partner ›See More Ways to Make Money   Amazon Payment Products Amazon Visa Amazon Store Card Amazon Secured Card Amazon Business Card Shop with Points Credit Card Marketplace Reload Your Balance Gift Cards Amazon Currency Converter   Let Us Help You Your Account Your Orders Shipping Rates & Policies Amazon Prime Returns & Replacements Manage Your Content and Devices Recalls and Product Safety Alerts Registry & Gift List Help   English United States Amazon Music Stream millions of songs Amazon Ads Reach customers wherever they spend their time 6pm Score deals on fashion brands AbeBooks Books, art & collectibles ACX Audiobook Publishing Made Easy Sell on Amazon Start a Selling Account Veeqo Shipping Software Inventory Management Amazon Business Everything For Your Business Amazon Fresh Groceries & More Right To Your Door AmazonGlobal Ship Orders Internationally Home Services Experienced Pros Happiness Guarantee Amazon Web Services Scalable Cloud Computing Services Audible Listen to Books & Original Audio Performances Box Office Mojo Find Movie Box Office Data Goo